tissueExpression.summary: Normal tissues displayed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining with additional nuclear positivity in small intestine, Purkinje cells, squamous epithelia and testis. Membranous staining was observed in stomach, bronchus and glandular cells of uterus. Small intestine and cells in granular layer of cerebellum exhibited strong immunoreactivity. Adrenocortical cells, hematopoietic tissue, breast, glial cells, liver, prostate and most of the lymphoid tissue were negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Medium consistency between antibody staining and RNA expression data
Partly consistent with extensive gene/protein characterization data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human small intestine shows strong cytoplasmic and nuclear positivity in glandular cells.

tissueExpression.summary: Few cases of colorectal cancers displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic staining with additional membranous and nuclear positivity in urothelial cancers. Occasional cases of pancreatic, endometrial, cervical and ovarian cancers were moderately stained. Remaining cancer tissues were weakly stained or negative.
